snippet: United States officials believe Russia may have tested a ground-launched cruise missile in violation of the 1987 Soviet-American treaty.
abstract: Obama administration is sending team of senior officials to Moscow to try to resolve American allegations that Russia violated landmark nuclear accord; at heart of dispute is allegation that Russia tested ground-launched cruise missile in violation of 1987 Soviet-American treaty banning intermediate-range missiles based on land.
lead_paragraph: United States officials believe Russia may have tested a ground-launched cruise missile in violation of the 1987 Soviet-American treaty.
